div.p: P67/474, unit 381, VPRS 3991 inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.

MS is annotated 'No 10' of 74 receipts covering materials supplied from the Botanic Garden for the Intercolonial Exhibition of Australasia, Melbourne, 1866-7, for which M was one of the Commissioners. Richmond Oct 30 1866
The Commissioners of the Intercolonial Exhibition per
To Modelling and Painting the following Fruits &c.
